meta {
  name: Update Lab Test
  type: http
  seq: 4
}

patch {
  url: {{baseUrl}}/master-data/{{masterDataId}}/lab-tests/{{labTestId}}
  body: json
  auth: bearer
}

headers {
  Content-Type: application/json
}

auth:bearer {
  token: {{businessAccessToken}}
}

body:json {
  {
    "testDisplayName": "CBC (Complete Blood Count)",
    "priceMaximum": 600,
    "commissionPrice": 60,
    "remarks": "Q3 price revision"
  }
}

docs {
  Patch a lab test's core fields (send only what changes). `versionHistory` is
  never edited here (use Add Version).
  
  Child sets are REPLACED when provided: include a full `samples` array and/or
  `resultParams` array (each param with its `referenceRanges`/`referenceValues`)
  to swap the whole set — the old active rows are soft-deleted and the new set
  created in one transaction. Omit a child array to leave it untouched.
  
  Same cross-field rules and conflicts as Create (422 `VALIDATION_ERROR`, 409 on
  name/code/parameterCode). 404 `LAB_TEST_NOT_FOUND` if missing/other tenant.
}
